tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I wanted to take a moment to Express my gratitude & provide a review regarding the dental treatment performed on me. I have visited national dental care for unbearable tooth pain,dr.Yugandhar garu & dr.sunehra has started looking into the issue & after examining 2 teeth are damaged they advised me to go for a rootcanal for 1 tooth and the other 1 was went for implant.

I was very scared of doing Rootcanal but after starting the treatment I got to know dr sunehra is expert on it.

foremost, i would like to commend your professionalism & expertise throughout the entire process.From the initial stage (consultation) to the final stage of the rootcanal treatment & implant treatment, you demonstrated a deep understanding of the procedure & consistently kept me well-informed and comfortable. Your ability to explain complex concepts in a clear manner made me feel at ease and confident.

The implant procedure itself was executed by dr
Srinivas with utmost care.your attention detail and commitment to achieving optimal results were evident every step of the way. I appreciate the way you took the time to assess my unique situation of the treatment plan to meet my specific needs.your expertise & experiences shine through,and I felt reassured knowing I was in safe hands.

Also, I want to appreciate the exceptional care i received from you and your staff. Your team was friendly, accommodating and efficient, making each visit a pleasant experience. The clinic environment was clean and well maintained,creating a comfortable atmosphere that contributed to my overall satisfaction.

All the best for the team NDCüëç

tags: Wait time,Value for money,Treatment satisfaction,Explanation of the health issue,Doctor friendliness,
review:
its been 2 years since my treatment. After 6-9 months i started some pain with the root canal. It gets healed itself after a month or so. I didn't find time to go back and get it treated. Later when i checked the prices. Treatment here is a costly than outside. Knowing all these I still took a chance and referred my in-laws for treatment there. *** ********* ** ********* *** **** **** * ***** ** ***** *** *** ********** When we took a step back they're speaking about the discount which they haven't provided me when I was treated. The patients who agree for the treatment will not get any discount here. If you say no to the treatment, thats when you'll get a discount. They do a lot of followups to get the treatment done.. they treat u so good that u can't say a no out of hesitation. They do a lot of followup for a 5 star rating on google reviews as well. When they handover the summary post treatment they'll for sure with a warm talk and nice smile ask for a 5 star review for which u hesitate again even to reduce a star.

I'm not against the clinic.. just asking everyone not to fall for the behavior, respect, smiles, etc. **** ** *** ***** ******* ***** **** ******* It's we who should be mindful and compare the cost, treatment and follow up reviews and then take a decision. You're spending a lot of hard earned money for your dental issues. Its no wrong in thinking twice in an effort to save. Please don't go here looking at these reviews. These are all exaggerated. Consider the 1 star and 2 star reviews as well and think wise.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
context: RCT - Root Canal Treatment,Zirconia Crowns,Ceramic Crowns and Bridges Fixing,
review:
National Dental Care - *Zero Pain Care Lounge*
Of all the dental clinics I visited so far in USA and in Hyderabad, NDC stands out. They truly live upto their tagline - Zero Pain care lounge. We generally associate dental problems and treatments with endless pain and sleepless nights. Well, not anymore. We have NDC to take care of our precious teeth. They treat your teeth like how you treat your baby-with Proper care and love. The moment you enter their clinic, you are warmly welcomed by desk staff and the doctor. Who knew dentists can be so pleasant in person. On your first visit, you will be thoroughly explained about your problem, various methods at arriving the solution  and the cost associated with each and every procedure. Dr Yugandhar will sit with you patiently and help you undertsand the process which suit your need and purse. Once you start taking treatment, you will receive so much personal care from the doctors (they will call you even at night to see how you are doing) you feel like you have become part of NDC family. Their patience, assurance they give you about the treatment and above all, the human touch they bring to the whole procedure is oh so overwhelming. I used to wait eagerly for my next appointment just to go and meet the doctors at NDC and have a pleasant time with them.I went to NDC with so much preconceived fear( because of the previous treatments which I had gone through at other clinics)and came out with a very comforting and confident smile . Thank you Dr Moulika, Dr Madhuri Dr Deepti and Dr Yugandhar gaaru for your valuable time and painless treatment. 
National Dental Care - not just a dental clinic but your family clinic for all your dental needs.
reply_text:
We're glad you had a  pleasant experience with us. Thank you for your valuable  feedback.
Hope to see you just for a check-up from now

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,
review:
They have putin their best efforts to maintain the hygiene, the equipment is of latest I guess. The consultation fee and Xray charges are reasonable considering their maintenance and equipment. Doctor was friendly and tried his best to explain what he wanted to. Staff was courtesies too. These guys are no less than a corporate hospital.

But no where, except here, I have seen an X ray given on a paper but not on a film. Even the paper on which doctor has written his suggestions and the cost of the treatment had been taken by the reception staff and did not allow to take it with me and the reason they sited was patients are loosing the files and that's why they aren't giving it to them. To some degree it' could be a valid reason but there are plenty of options. Right ? They have everything online so nothing will happen even if a patient lost the entire file.

An other patient who got some treatment said that it was really of less pain and for those who don't bother much about money it's one of the best places.

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
*** **** ******** ** *** *****You get a great welcome when you visit first time.Once you start taking service you will get to know real issues.

****** ******** ****** ********I am currently availing root canal service here and Doctor Lakshmi is doing it.Met doctor Yugandar on first visit.Discussion with him is mostly on high level and cost of root canal.
Initially started with 4 root canal and 2 filling and now 8 rct and 3 filling.

They do not book appointments properly.Do not explain exact cost when they do new service.Cost keeps on increasing.As you start making payments service becomes casual.

Today I have appointment at 3 pm but they have no idea when I called them 30 minutes before.Simply they ask me to come at different time.This is 2nd time in 4th visit.No responsibility.

They have given appointment with different patient as I already paid 80% cost *** **** *** ** **** ** ***** *** *****Infact they wanted me to pay full cost in last 2 visits but I said I will pay as and when service starts.

****** ******* ** ******* *** this unprofessional behaviour is due to management ** ****** ** ****************** ** ******** ******** ** ********* ** *******
Sorry state of affairs considering they have right facilities and doctor.

review:
We have visited NDC for my Wisdom tooth extraction and RCT with crown treatment.
We were given a clear picture of the situation then and were suggested for a RCT and crown implant first then in the later month were suggested to go for extraction.
Why you should visit NDC?
1.Experienced staff with service minded attitude.
2.Very resonable charges.
3.In house eqipment,No need to wander for xray etc outside.
TREATMENT
1.RCT and crown

Doctor was very well experienced all went well without any pain.Very top class facilities and services.

2.Extraction 

Two teeth were extracted in just about 15 mins.Never had any pain later point as well.Zero pain caption is apt for the Clinic.
If ur in madinaguda or chandanagar or any near by areas this should be your clinic for any dentistry issues.
Thank you Dr Swetha for taking us through the process with great care and helping us with the whole process.Thank you the NDC team for the best of service.

review: I have visited the National Dental Care, Madinaguda branch for my wife's teeth problem actually there was not one, but many issues with her teeth.   Based on the reviews on the practo we went to this hospital as a second opinion.  In the first meeting itself we were very much impressed by Dr. Yugandhar sir's approach towards the patient, very clear explanation and friendly nature.  It was covid time and we were skeptical about to get the treatment or not, but the hospital is very clean and maintains all the hygiene which is required during covid time. Thank you Yugandhar sir and the staff for the treatment provided.   Moreover the price for the treatment was also reasonable.

review: How I wish all my hospital experience were same as National Dental Care..! First thing you notice here is the cleanliness and a lounge like waiting area..calms down your nerve immediately. You are offered mineral water and a cup of coffee by a smiling staff..take that..! You meet an expert doctor that explains you the process in every detail and removes any anxiety. You experience the  state of the art machinery where you can see the insides of your teeth on a LCD display. This was the 1st time I saw my teeth and understood the extent of the problem. Then you go through the painless experience during the treatment where they clearly explain at each step. At the billing time, you are pleasantly surprised to notice that they didn't charge you for consultancy, or X-ray...and they give you all medicines that they prescribed...free of cost. I am still finding it all hard to believe. All in all...5 Star Experience..!!
